label: Horizontal Line
description: Lays elements out horizontally according to the aggregate width of prior nodes.

label: Vertical Line
description: Lays elements out vertically according to the aggregate height of prior nodes.

label: Grid Layout
description: Sets up a grid based on the configured width, height, number of rows and number of columns.

label: Flow Layout
description: Takes elements of various sizes and fits them as closely as possible within the bounds specified.

label: Stack Layout
description: Sets elements in a stacked series based on order.

label: Wave Layout
description: Places elements in a sine, cosine tan or other trigonometric wave functions. Rotation of elements can align to the path of the wave.
